flowRoot.flowPara: Norepinephrine (or noradrenalin) was discovered in 1946 by von Euler. It is strongly associated with bringing our nervous system into "high alert". It is prevalent in the sympathetic system. It increases heart rate and blood pressure. It is released by adrenal glands into the blood stream, along with its close relative epinephrine (aka adrenalin). It is also important for forming memories. Stress tends to deplete our store of adrenalin, while exercise tends to increase it. Amphetamines work by causing the release of norepinephrine, as well as dopamine and serotonin..
